        <section>
            <title>The Correlation Coefficient&#8212;r</title>
            <body>
                <p>The numerical measure that assesses the strength of a linear relationship is
                    called the <em>correlation coefficient</em> and is denoted by <em>r</em>. We
                    will</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Define the correlation r.</li>
                    <li>Discuss the calculation of r.</li>
                    <li>Explain how to interpret the value of r.</li>
                    <li>Talk about some of the properties of r. </li>
                </ul>
                
                <p>
                    <em>Definition: </em> The correlation
                    coefficient (r) is a numerical measure that measures the
                    <em>strength</em> and <em>direction</em>
                    of a linear relationship between two quantitative variables. </p>
                <p>
                    <em>Calculation: </em>r is calculated using the following formula: <m:math
                        overflow="scroll">
                        <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                        <m:mfrac>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                            </m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:mfrac>
                        <m:munderover>
                            <m:mo>∑</m:mo>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                                <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                            </m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:mi>n</m:mi>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:munderover>
                        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                        <m:mfrac>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:msub>
                                    <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                </m:msub>
                                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                                <m:mover accent="true">
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                    <m:mo>¯</m:mo>
                                </m:mover>
                            </m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:msub>
                                    <m:mi>S</m:mi>
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mi>x</m:mi>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                </m:msub>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:mfrac>
                        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                        <m:mfrac>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:msub>
                                    <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mi>i</m:mi>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                </m:msub>
                                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                                <m:mover accent="true">
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                    <m:mo>¯</m:mo>
                                </m:mover>
                            </m:mrow>
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:msub>
                                    <m:mi>S</m:mi>
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mi>y</m:mi>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                </m:msub>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:mfrac>
                        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:math>
                </p>
                <p>However, the calculation of the correlation (r) is not the focus of this course.
                    We will use a statistics package to calculate r for us, and the
                    emphasis of this course is on the <em style="italic">interpretation</em> of its
                    value. </p>
            </body>
        </section>
